You are working on the CryptoVault crypto dashboard project.
This project has a complete design system with CSS custom properties (tokens).
ALL UI creation MUST follow these rules — they are implicit in every request.

# Mandatory Rules

1. ALL colors via CSS tokens from theme/dark.css + theme/light.css — NEVER hardcoded hex
2. ALL components use existing classes from theme/components.css (~1700 lines)
3. Every page uses the sidebar+topbar layout from existing pages (analytics.html, products.html, etc.)
4. Dark theme is default (data-theme="dark"), light theme MUST also work
5. Font: Inter (Google Fonts), weights 400-700
6. Typography scale: --text-display(28), --text-lg(22), --text-title(20), --text-heading(18), --text-subheading(15), --text-body(14), --text-sm(13), --text-caption(12), --text-xs(11)
7. Spacing scale: --space-xs(4) through --space-3xl(32) — no arbitrary values
8. Border radius: --radius-xs(6) through --radius-pill(9999)
9. Transitions: var(--ease-out) — never ease, linear, etc.
10. White text on solid backgrounds: var(--on-solid) — never #fff
11. SVG icons inline with currentColor
12. Chart legends: always custom HTML (legend: { display: false } in Chart.js)
13. Stat indicator rows: always with background var(--muted)
14. Focus visible: outline 2px solid var(--ring), offset 2px

# CSS Prefixes

- .kpi- (KPI cards) | .tbl- (tables) | .dw- (drawer) | .ch- (charts)
- .od- (order detail) | .od-detail- (detail sections) | .ch-lg- (legends)
- .btn / .btn--* (buttons) | .badge / .status-chip (badges)

# Reference Pages

- analytics.html: KPI grid, table+drawer, chart cards, stat sub-cards
- products.html: Table with toolbar (tabs, search, filter, export), pagination
- order-detail.html: Tabs, 2-column grid, detail sections, field grids, tags, timeline
- market-trends.html: Chart cards, stat rows, 3 legend types, filter bar, sparklines

# Build

npx @tailwindcss/cli -i theme/main.css -o dist/styles.css --minify

# MCP Server

The project includes a design system MCP server at igreendashboard-design-mcp/.
Use it for token lookup, CSS validation, component specs, and page templates.
